\p{Status: \strong{design}. Altium-first reverse-engineering package for the 8-node oscillator Ising machine (Bowring/Anderson/Tiffany), reconstructed from the paper/blog because author board files are not available. The KiCad reconstruction is locally verified openable and exportable (DRC clean, unrouted logical nets left explicit); exact MPNs, footprints, board spacing, and production routing remain unconfirmed pending an author response.}
\p{Source lives in an external repo, not vendored into this forest: github.com/monaduck1069/bci-pcb-ising at ed7c029. A local working copy sits at bci/pcb/ising/ (its own git, gitignored here). The board-files request draft and provenance notes are under docs/ in that repo.}
\p{Related: [[bci-indeterminate-spares]] (hardware-builds audit). This atom is the canonical forest reference for the OIM PCB; the design package itself is versioned in its own repo.}
